    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-07-01T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-07-01T01:00:00-05:00" n="306"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d306">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2176</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MRS1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-07-01T15:00:00+09:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 1, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received July 2, 9 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following the occupation of Vladivostok by the Czech forces on the 29th, fully
                    reported by <persName corresp="#p_KAAM1">Admiral Knight</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_CJK1">Caldwell</persName>,<note n="2" xml:id="d306fn2">See
                        telegram of June 29 from the Consul at Vladivostok, <hi rend="italic"
                            >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_235">p. 235</ref>.</note> the French
                    Government to-day requested the Japanese Government to lend to the Czech army 30
                    machine guns and a number of mountain batteries with the necessary ammunition to
                    prevent a possible counter attack by the Red Guard. The Japanese Government is
                    considering this request, but appears inclined to answer that it does not feel
                    justified in taking any action until the Allies and the United States are agreed
                    on a general plan to be adopted in meeting the situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_MRS1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
